cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the stability properties of nonlinear multi-task regression in reproducing Hilbert spaces with operator-valued kernels. The paper discusses learning problems with nonscalar outputs like multi-task learning and structured output prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses various multi-task kernel regression methods such as vector-valued SVR and functional ridge regression, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also discusses generalization bounds, which are relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
